title: Norway Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Norway Three Month Interbank Rate was at 3.38 percent on Thursday November 10. Interbank Rate in Norway averaged 5.24 percent from 1986 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 27.21 percent in November of 1992 and a record low of 0.19 percent in June of 2021. The NIBOR (Norwegian Inter-Bank Offer Rate) is an the interest rate that the banks charge each other for loans. This page provides - Norway Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Norske Finansielle Referanser AS
